00:23:56.578 --> 00:24:02.940 align:middle line:90%


00:24:02.940 --> 00:24:07.030 align:middle line:84%
>> 50 years ago, we were trying
to understand the electron.

00:24:07.030 --> 00:24:09.000 align:middle line:84%
And for God sakes,
the thing turns out

00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:11.730 align:middle line:90%
to be a wave function, OK?

00:24:11.730 --> 00:24:12.960 align:middle line:90%
It's a wave.

00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:14.250 align:middle line:90%
You can't localize it.

00:24:14.250 --> 00:24:15.410 align:middle line:90%
You try to localize it.

00:24:15.410 --> 00:24:16.952 align:middle line:84%
It really slips
through your fingers.

00:24:16.952 --> 00:24:18.840 align:middle line:90%
It's impossible to localize.

00:24:18.840 --> 00:24:20.730 align:middle line:84%
So for a while we
got used to the fact

00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:23.370 align:middle line:84%
that, OK, there are no
particles ultimately,

00:24:23.370 --> 00:24:24.720 align:middle line:90%
there are just waves.

00:24:24.720 --> 00:24:26.910 align:middle line:90%
It's called a wave function.

00:24:26.910 --> 00:24:28.830 align:middle line:84%
When you go deeper into
physics and you really

00:24:28.830 --> 00:24:31.870 align:middle line:84%
try to get a handle on
what the wave function is,

00:24:31.870 --> 00:24:33.930 align:middle line:90%
you localize that wave.

00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:36.300 align:middle line:84%
And the waves slips
through your fingers,

00:24:36.300 --> 00:24:39.330 align:middle line:84%
because the wave actually
gets replaced in quantum field

00:24:39.330 --> 00:24:42.030 align:middle line:84%
theory with something
more abstract

00:24:42.030 --> 00:24:43.830 align:middle line:90%
that doesn't even have a shape.

00:24:43.830 --> 00:24:47.550 align:middle line:84%
It must be described instead
as a simultaneous coexistence

00:24:47.550 --> 00:24:49.770 align:middle line:90%
of all possible shapes.

00:24:49.770 --> 00:24:51.400 align:middle line:84%
It's not even a
self-respecting wave.

00:24:51.400 --> 00:24:53.025 align:middle line:84%
It's something more
abstract than that.

00:24:53.025 --> 00:24:55.140 align:middle line:84%
It has slipped through
your fingers again.

00:24:55.140 --> 00:24:57.900 align:middle line:10%
And then when you get
beyond quantum field theory

00:24:57.900 --> 00:25:01.560 align:middle line:10%
to unified field theory,
you try to even grasp

00:25:01.560 --> 00:25:03.330 align:middle line:10%
the nature of that
quantum field, which

00:25:03.330 --> 00:25:05.400 align:middle line:10%
is already abstract,
and you end up

00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:07.590 align:middle line:10%
with something
that's pure being,

00:25:07.590 --> 00:25:10.740 align:middle line:10%
absolutely beyond the
intellect to even describe,

00:25:10.740 --> 00:25:14.640 align:middle line:10%
pure abstractness, pure
potentiality, pure existence.

00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:17.430 align:middle line:90%


00:25:17.430 --> 00:25:21.420 align:middle line:84%
>> But the great great
granddaddy of wacky quantum

00:25:21.420 --> 00:25:24.870 align:middle line:90%
weirdness is entanglement.

00:25:24.870 --> 00:25:30.270 align:middle line:84%
If time reversal symmetry
destroys the notion of time,

00:25:30.270 --> 00:25:34.440 align:middle line:84%
then entanglement crushes
our experience of space.

00:25:34.440 --> 00:25:40.680 align:middle line:84%
Two objects, two electrons
created together are entangled.

00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:43.830 align:middle line:84%
Send one to the other
side of the universe.

00:25:43.830 --> 00:25:47.310 align:middle line:90%


00:25:47.310 --> 00:25:54.780 align:middle line:84%
Now, do something to one and
the other responds instantly.

00:25:54.780 --> 00:25:56.940 align:middle line:90%
Instantly.

00:25:56.940 --> 00:26:00.750 align:middle line:84%
So either information is
traveling infinitely fast

00:26:00.750 --> 00:26:05.970 align:middle line:84%
or, in reality, they
are still connected.

00:26:05.970 --> 00:26:08.670 align:middle line:90%
They are entangled.

00:26:08.670 --> 00:26:14.250 align:middle line:84%
And since everything was
entangled at the moment

00:26:14.250 --> 00:26:20.760 align:middle line:84%
of the Big Bang, that means
everything is still touching.

00:26:20.760 --> 00:26:25.860 align:middle line:84%
Space is just the construct that
gives the illusion that there

00:26:25.860 --> 00:26:29.070 align:middle line:90%
are separate objects.

00:26:29.070 --> 00:26:31.730 align:middle line:84%
Are we far enough down
the rabbit hole yet?

00:26:31.730 --> 00:26:36.570 align:middle line:90%


00:26:36.570 --> 00:26:40.660 align:middle line:84%
>> To go down the rabbit
hole and to get away from

00:26:40.660 --> 00:26:43.570 align:middle line:90%
the mundane is thrilling.

00:26:43.570 --> 00:26:46.630 align:middle line:84%
Everybody secretly
is an adventurer.

00:26:46.630 --> 00:26:49.600 align:middle line:84%
When we head down
a rabbit hole, we

00:26:49.600 --> 00:26:52.390 align:middle line:84%
have to reformat
all of our knowledge

00:26:52.390 --> 00:26:54.130 align:middle line:84%
and our present
understanding and we

00:26:54.130 --> 00:26:58.790 align:middle line:84%
have to be able to combine
knowledge in a different way

00:26:58.790 --> 00:27:01.360 align:middle line:84%
than we've processed
it up to this point.

00:27:01.360 --> 00:27:04.180 align:middle line:84%
It means that we have
to step outside the box

00:27:04.180 --> 00:27:07.690 align:middle line:84%
of our most familiar, most
common way of thinking.

00:27:07.690 --> 00:27:12.998 align:middle line:84%
We have to begin to perceive the
question or the understanding

00:27:12.998 --> 00:27:14.290 align:middle line:90%
from a different point of view.

00:27:14.290 --> 00:27:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And in order to
do that, you have

00:27:16.540 --> 00:27:18.970 align:middle line:90%
to mix circuits in the brain.

00:27:18.970 --> 00:27:20.000 align:middle line:90%
>> It's tricky.

00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:21.920 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you
want to go there.

00:27:21.920 --> 00:27:24.450 align:middle line:90%
You do want to go there?

00:27:24.450 --> 00:27:29.750 align:middle line:84%
So entanglement is space
separated and time separated.

00:27:29.750 --> 00:27:31.700 align:middle line:84%
One way of looking
very specifically

00:27:31.700 --> 00:27:34.520 align:middle line:84%
at the time separation
aspect, it's

00:27:34.520 --> 00:27:38.630 align:middle line:84%
much easier to do this with
one individual rather than two.

00:27:38.630 --> 00:27:41.640 align:middle line:84%
Because who are you better
entangled with than anyone?

00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:42.440 align:middle line:90%
It's yourself.

00:27:42.440 --> 00:27:44.840 align:middle line:84%
It's your future self
that you're entangled with

00:27:44.840 --> 00:27:46.340 align:middle line:90%
and your past self.

00:27:46.340 --> 00:27:49.610 align:middle line:84%
So the experiment that I
developed to look at this

00:27:49.610 --> 00:27:52.700 align:middle line:84%
is we wire you up,
typically to look

00:27:52.700 --> 00:27:54.260 align:middle line:84%
at skin conductance
but also heart

00:27:54.260 --> 00:27:56.910 align:middle line:90%
rate and other parameters.

00:27:56.910 --> 00:27:59.730 align:middle line:84%
You will sit in front
of a computer screen

00:27:59.730 --> 00:28:00.987 align:middle line:90%
and you press a button.

00:28:00.987 --> 00:28:02.820 align:middle line:84%
And you know that five
seconds later, you're

00:28:02.820 --> 00:28:04.183 align:middle line:90%
going to see a picture.

00:28:04.183 --> 00:28:05.850 align:middle line:84%
It could a very calm
picture or it might

00:28:05.850 --> 00:28:07.620 align:middle line:90%
be a very emotional picture.

00:28:07.620 --> 00:28:10.110 align:middle line:84%
And it's randomly
selected by the computer

00:28:10.110 --> 00:28:12.283 align:middle line:90%
immediately before it's shown.

00:28:12.283 --> 00:28:13.950 align:middle line:84%
So when you press the
button, the future

00:28:13.950 --> 00:28:16.050 align:middle line:90%
is not yet determined.

00:28:16.050 --> 00:28:18.060 align:middle line:84%
So you would need
real precognition

00:28:18.060 --> 00:28:21.230 align:middle line:84%
in order to be able to jump into
the future and get it somehow.

00:28:21.230 --> 00:28:22.980 align:middle line:84%
So since we're looking
at your physiology,

00:28:22.980 --> 00:28:25.110 align:middle line:84%
we know what happens
to physiology after you

00:28:25.110 --> 00:28:26.620 align:middle line:90%
see an emotional image.

00:28:26.620 --> 00:28:28.800 align:middle line:84%
And we know what happens
after you see a calm image.

00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:31.320 align:middle line:84%
The question is, does
that future experience

00:28:31.320 --> 00:28:33.720 align:middle line:90%
leak into your present?

00:28:33.720 --> 00:28:36.480 align:middle line:84%
Does it happen before
you see the picture?

00:28:36.480 --> 00:28:38.940 align:middle line:84%
And through this experiment,
you can see what happens.

00:28:38.940 --> 00:28:42.360 align:middle line:84%
Electrical activity
of the heart, EKG.

00:28:42.360 --> 00:28:43.830 align:middle line:84%
This is
photoplethysmograph, which

00:28:43.830 --> 00:28:47.940 align:middle line:84%
is the amount of blood in the
fingertip, and respiration,

00:28:47.940 --> 00:28:49.630 align:middle line:90%
breathing in, breathing out.

00:28:49.630 --> 00:28:50.430 align:middle line:90%
Press the button.

00:28:50.430 --> 00:28:51.805 align:middle line:84%
Well, what happens
to physiology?

00:28:51.805 --> 00:28:55.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, if it starts rising
before the image appears,

00:28:55.500 --> 00:28:59.583 align:middle line:84%
it may suggest that you're about
to get an emotional picture.

00:28:59.583 --> 00:29:01.500 align:middle line:84%
And if it stays calm,
it suggests maybe you're

00:29:01.500 --> 00:29:02.890 align:middle line:90%
going to get a calm picture.

00:29:02.890 --> 00:29:05.340 align:middle line:84%
So we've done this
kind of experiment

00:29:05.340 --> 00:29:07.650 align:middle line:84%
for several hundred
people, and colleagues have

00:29:07.650 --> 00:29:09.520 align:middle line:90%
run this experiment as well.

00:29:09.520 --> 00:29:12.450 align:middle line:84%
And as it turns out, that
is exactly what you see.

00:29:12.450 --> 00:29:16.260 align:middle line:84%
People become aroused before
randomly selected pictures

00:29:16.260 --> 00:29:18.840 align:middle line:84%
in the future that
happen to be emotional

00:29:18.840 --> 00:29:21.990 align:middle line:84%
and they remain calm before
randomly selected pictures that

00:29:21.990 --> 00:29:23.660 align:middle line:90%
are calm.

00:29:23.660 --> 00:29:27.500 align:middle line:84%
This has been seen in heart rate
changes, in skin conductance,

00:29:27.500 --> 00:29:30.290 align:middle line:84%
in the brain, and
basically systemically

00:29:30.290 --> 00:29:31.370 align:middle line:90%
throughout the body.

00:29:31.370 --> 00:29:33.740 align:middle line:84%
We are entangled with
our future selves.

00:29:33.740 --> 00:29:36.500 align:middle line:90%


00:29:36.500 --> 00:29:38.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Wormholes, or
topological fluctuations,

00:29:38.840 --> 00:29:42.710 align:middle line:84%
really channels of communication
that connect distant parts

00:29:42.710 --> 00:29:44.900 align:middle line:90%
of the universe instantaneously.

00:29:44.900 --> 00:29:46.670 align:middle line:90%
Even time travel is possible.

00:29:46.670 --> 00:29:50.180 align:middle line:84%
>> The way I understand the
rabbit hole is that it is

00:29:50.180 --> 00:29:54.950 align:middle line:90%
